Package: com.github.tagc.semver.version

[Groovy] Interface Version

  • Represents a semantic version number for a project.

    Version objects are immutable. They can be compared based on the standard for semantic version comparisons (based on lexicographic comparison of major, minor and patch numbers).

    Instances of Version ought to be compared using Java's java.lang.Object#equals method in preference to Groovy's '==' equality checks.

    Authors:
    davidfallah
    Since:
    v0.1.0

      • Category distanceFrom(Version newerVersion)

        Returns the category of this version that would have to be bumped in order to get newerVersion.

        This method will return a particular Version.Category if and only if bumping this version by only that category by one increment will result in newVersion.

        In the case that no category satisfies these criteria, null is returned.

        Returns:
        the difference in category that separates this version and newerVersion or null if none satisfy the criteria
        Parameters:
        newerVersion - an instance of Version that is newer according to Semantic versioning logic
